snippet.title: New bill to improve amber alert system heard by Missouri House committee
snippet.description:
JEFFERSON CITY - Missouri lawmakers hope to pass a bill that would improve the state's amber alert system. A House committee heard the bill, known as Hailey's Law, this afternoon.  The bill has already passed through the Senate, and sponsored by Springfield's Eric Burlison. 

"The system failed a young girl that day," Senator Eric Burlison said. "And this is the result of trying to attempt to find out what failed in that system and how to address it." 

Hailey's law is named after Hailey Owens, a 10-year-old girl who was abducted and killed by Craig Wood In Springfield in 2014.

snippet.title: Missy Elliot -Throw it Back - REVERSED - Amber Alert
snippet.description:
This is a very advanced reverse. Both because of speaking patterns that change very slightly,
and because of many words and phrases that sound the same but are just one minute bit different. 
The symbolism carries through very well, however. Those of you who are familiar with my videos understand the symbolism between the Hair and the Heritage in dreams, and embedded deep in the human psyche. You can imagine the psychological symbolism of have "Fake Hair" then. or being "Bald".

But there are actually 2 or three underlying stories. 
Missy describes being found by "Lesbian Feminists" who showed up to her "Dancefloor" and not only didn't dance But stopped all of the dancing because they don't dance. They offered good money and so "bought her voice" They want to fight skinny women over the "Boy" and Missy describes "Grabbing popcorn and watching", she thinks it is entertaining because it is an impossible fight, men are attracted to thin women. These same women idolize Missy because she is not affected by this, but in her own words, she's still at "School" learning a lesson and gives the advice to "Eat Right", "work out" and then just say "Hi, hi, hi, hi".

When I do a reverse I not only pay attention to the audio, but I get to see every frame in the video.
Pedophilia is both referenced in the Lyric of reversed speech and In video by the Girl with the Pizza Purse who ushers the fatter girl into "Missy Land". If you have heard about MKULTRA the british alter is the most common one created amongst MK alters @4:54

There are several side arcs including a story about a Woman who pays a "Fag" to make her pregnant, and then the "Fag" later "Sues her" for custody of the child. This is not a reverse for the feint of heart, or the weak minded. There is an awful lot to unpack with this one.

The "Wizards" or Produces of the video, were shooting for a "Spell" or a scene of "Bring your weave, we a rich nigga". But "The Owl, forgetful and the will deep winning". @1:32
The "Deep will" for a way out of this mess is what has changed the actual meaning from the Producer's intent.

"Amber Alert" is a call for help to the people, when a child has gone missing. Over 50% of black children are aborted, The social acceptability of Homosexuality has become the new pillar that pedophiles stand on.
This is an amazing point brought up by this video, The widespreadness of Homosexuality, is a counter swing
caused by the "War between men and women". Of which, even in Missy's words "She patented", was the pioneer of some of these ideas which caused harm. Because women "Stole" and committed "Sin" they become "Bald". No Heritage, no lineage. The idea of men as "Slaves" is portrayed visually (By them being the motive force of the Vehicle) an allegory for financial slavery of men, using "Divorce" as a toy.  In the war of men and women, the war is not one of the "Gun" @2:43
The school is shown as "Choices, waste your time", women are warned by her that they are "To slow" to have children. If they wait too long their "Hair grow old" and eventually they run out of time at all for children. In later verses she says they "had no-one" and end up all alone. Perhaps something that She is still in the process of learning herself because she admits "She still at school" too.

"Here is Help" Missy says with a good number of the pre-chorus lines. But even within the lyric her reverse mind tells us she shouldn't really be commended. She's a sinner, and on this one tiny issue, is on the side of good in the war, but on many other things she has caused much harm with her platform. It is a Mirror to KRS ONE, where he has a mostly positive and good track record but one one or two issues does harm, Missy has a mostly negative track record but on this does very good. Even though she is being hired by these people, she doesn't agree with them, and they don't understand her music or even what she is about. Her thoughts are, don't lash out at the pretty girl because she gets the boy, work out, eat right, and go and say hi. This may be a lesson learned from her own personal life, because I bet once she lost a little weight, she felt the male attention increase in her own life.
@2:24 "Blister ya, but Jam with this little Issue."

snippet.title: Amber Alert for abducted 11 year old from Peel Region OPP COMMS.  Feb 14-15, 2019
snippet.description:
I was watching youtube as i heard my cell phone make an Amber alert about a missing 11 year old.  I quickly turned on my scanner and recorded.   
The OPP pinged his cell and it last pinged in Pickering at Port Union and 401 hiway around 9pm today.
Later a vehicle driving north on hiway 400 spotted the suspect vehicle in question and OPP came from Barrie and Orillia. townships.
The OPP did a high risk take down.
Vehicle seized and OPP in Communication now with Peel police.

This was an abduction but on the radio the dispatcher advised the suspect is wanted for Homicide.    

Child found dead in a Brampton home.    

Last 10 minutes of the COMMS are quiet but i was recording, you can skip it.   No time to edit.    This is in real time COMMS.


Const. Akil Mooken said the pair were together to celebrate the daughter‚Äôs birthday but when the time came to bring her back to the mother, who has custody, they didn‚Äôt show up. Comments were made by Rajkumar to the mother indicating he could cause harm to himself and his daughter.

‚ÄúWe have concerns for both Riya and Roopesh,‚Äù Mooken said. ‚ÄúWe are asking the public for assistance in helping to locate both of these individuals.‚Äù

Emergency Management Ontario followed Peel‚Äôs original report of the abduction with an emergency alert deployed to mobile devices just after 11:30 p.m.

Police said Roopesh Rajkumar is operating a silver, two-door Honda Civic with a plate number ARBV 598. They were last seen in the area of Hurontario Rd. and Derry Rd. in Mississauga.

Riya Rajkumar is described as brown, four feet, 60 lbs., thin build, with below shoulder length black hair. She was last wearing a pink dress with hearts, black boots, black tights, black jacket with fur-lined hood. She also has a black and white purse with a pink heart that has an R in it.

Peel police have confirmed they working with the Ontario Provincial Police on the investigation.


UPDATE.....

CHILD FOUND DEAD IN A BRAMPTON HOME...

For any copyright, please send me a message.  ¬†Hollywood actress Amber Heard is joining forces with former Prime Minister's wife Cherie Blair to campaign against people being unfairly jailed. ¬†The film star, who has traded domestic abuse allegations with ex-husband Johnny Depp, which both deny, will speak on the same stage as human rights QC Mrs Blair at the United Nations. ¬†Aqauman star Heard, 33, is a United Nations ambassador on human rights. ¬†She and Mrs Blair will speak at the UN General Assembly in New York next week to highlight the case of a Russian-born businesswoman, Marsha Lazareva, who was held in a Kuwaiti prison for 470 days. ¬†Ms Lazareva was sentenced to 10 years' jail with hard labour after being found guilty of embezzlement by a Kuwait court last year.  ¬†Supporters claim Ms Lazareva was incarcerated in a ‚Äúshow trial‚Äù over a major port investment. ¬†Prosecutors accused her of embezzling money but, according to her allies, it was in fact frozen in the United Arab Emirates and has since been released to all investors.  ¬†Her supporters have also complained about her treatment at the hands of the Kuwaiti authorities while she was held. ¬†Mrs Blair, who lived in Downing Street from 1997 to 2007, said: ‚ÄúArbitrary detention continues to be ignored. ¬†‚ÄúI will highlight the Marsha Lazareva case, but international law is flouted the world over and the international community must do more to tackle this outrage.‚Äù

snippet.title: Amber Heard weird life story / LGBT, relationships
snippet.description:
Amber Heard was married to her The Rum Diary co-star Johnny Depp. However they divorced and that divorce drew significant media attention, as she alleged that he was physically and verbally abusive towards her through most of their relationship. 
In 2017 she made an appearance in the superhero film Justice League . She reprised the latter role opposite Jason Momoa in Aquaman , which became the fifth most profitable DC Extended Universe film. The same year, Heard was also named a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant L'Or√©al Paris. In 2019, she appeared in supporting roles in the independent films Her Smell and Gully.
In addition to her acting career, Heard engages in activism for causes such as LGBTQ rights and domestic and sexual violence awareness. She is an American Civil Liberties Union ambassador and has been named a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.
Amber Heard dropped out of high school, eventually earning a diploma through a home-study course. When Heard was 16, her best friend died in a car crash; Heard, who was raised Catholic, subsequently declared herself an atheist. She once has stated, "I don't label myself one way or another‚ÄîI have had successful relationships with men and now a woman. I love who I love; it's the person that matters.
After several unsuccessful films, Heard appeared in the box office successes 3 Days to Kill , Magic Mike XXL   and The Danish Girl . She also starred in the television musical drama One More Time , and the London Fields .

Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amber_Heard

snippet.title: While patriarchal dominance models rule us all, Johnny Depp's tale is every battered man's tale
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp was not a perpetrator of DV against Amber Heard; he was a victim of DV by her: https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2019/03/13/johnny-depp-accuses-amber-heard-abuse.html

On Patriarchal Dominance Models: For close to half a century, gynocentric gender ideologues have institutionalised approaches to combating abuse which are solely based on Patriarchal Dominance models. Patriarchal Dominance models dogmatically and arbitrarily decree that ALL abuse is "a manifestation of the oppression of women and the product of patriarchal [ie exclusively male] power" - "where women are only victims and only males are perpetrators" - where "males can never be oppressed [and therefore can never be 'real' victims]. The only abuse dynamic which this model is capable of accurately recognising is male-on-female abuse. 

With same-sex violence and abuse, this model is as homophobic as the Westboro Baptist Church. It responds to male-on-male partner violence by condescendingly dismissing it as "[just] male privilege backfiring" and "just men doing it to each other [so both parties, including the victim, need to address their toxic masculinity]". It responds to female victims of same-sex partner violence by treating them like pathological liars, because "women are only victims and only males are perpetrators". This is a perpetual hate crime against abused members of the LGBTIQ+ community. 

Worse still, in cases of female-on-male abuse, as the only party capable of experiencing "the oppression of women" is the abuser and the only party capable of possessing "[male] power" is the victim, these models not only blame the victim, but accuse the victim of "oppressing their abusers into abusing them? This is the sole position of female abusers (including child abusers, paedophiles, rapists and batterers), their excusers and their enablers. 

Worst of all, as people with a disability and especially disabled children have no real power, in cases of female-on-male abuse involving abused disabled men and abused disabled boys, these models essentially argue that the mere existence of said disabled abuse victim "oppressed their abusers into abusing them". This is the very argument the Nazis used to create a culture of collective and systemic abuse against the disabled, as a precursor to rounding them up into "research hospitals" and butchering them as guinea pigs to make the Final Solution a reality. In short, not only are patriarchal dominance models the argument of a Nazi in their ableism ‚Äî they're literally tantamount to Holocaust Incitement.

"Congo‚Äôs Forgotten Curse: Epidemic of Female-on-Female Rape": http://world.time.com/2013/12/03/congos-forgotten-curse-epidemic-of-female-on-female-rape/

"Domestic violence support services failing lesbians": http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/national-news/new-south-wales-news/domestic-violence-support-services-failing-lesbians/140608

Male stat rape victims made to pay child support to their abusers: http://web.archive.org/web/20170507044705/http://www.ageofconsent.com/comments/numberthirtysix.htm

"Pedophile support programs challenge community hatred": 
https://www.smh.com.au/national/pedophile-support-programs-challenge-community-hatred-20140328-35ofk.html

"Finally, there is an alarmingly high rate of sexual abuse by females in thebackgrounds of rapists, sex offenders and sexually aggressive men ‚Äì 59%(Petrovich and Templer, 1984), 66% (Groth, 1979) and 80% (Briere andSmiljanich, 1993). A strong case for the need to identify female perpetrators canbe found in Table 4, which presents the findings from a study of adolescent sexoffenders by O‚ÄôBrien (1989). Male adolescent sex offenders abused by ‚Äúfemalesonly‚Äù chose female victims almost exclusively. " (Page 30): https://canadiancrc.com/PDFs/The_Invisible_Boy_Report.pdf (Page 30)

snippet.title: Amber Heard | Aquaman | Hot Tribute | Viral Productions
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige Heard (n√©e Parsons), an internet researcher, and David C. Heard (David Clinton Heard), a contractor. She has English, Irish, Scottish, German, and Welsh ancestry.

Heard appeared in the Academy Award-nominated film, North Country (2005), in which she played Charlize Theron's character in flashbacks. Her other early film credits include: Syrup (2013), Drive Angry (2011) 3D, The Joneses (2009), Never Back Down (2008), Alpha Dog (2006) and Friday Night Lights (2004). On television, Heard starred on The CW drama, Hidden Palms (2007), and had guest starring roles on Showtime's Californication (2007) and CBS's Criminal Minds (2005).

In 2009, Heard starred in the box office hit, Zombieland (2009), opposite Woody Harrelson, Bill Murray and Jesse Eisenberg. She also starred in the suspense thriller, The Stepfather (2009), with Sela Ward, Dylan Walsh and Penn Badgley. In 2008, she garnered attention for her role in the comedic hit, Pineapple Express (2008), with Seth Rogen and James Franco. Heard received a 2008 Young Hollywood Award for her breakthrough performance in "Pineapple Express".

She appeared in The Rum Diary (2011), opposite Johnny Depp, and John Carpenter's The Ward (2010), which premiered at the 2010 Toronto Film Festival. She also starred in the independent film, And Soon the Darkness (2010), in which she additionally served as a co-producer.

Heard starred in Paranoia (2013), opposite Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth and Gary Oldman. The film was released by "Relativity Media" on August 16, 2013. She also starred in Robert Rodriguez's Machete Kills (2013), which was released by "Open Road Films" on March 4, 2013, and McG's 3 Days to Kill (2014), opposite Kevin Costner and Hailee Steinfeld, which was released in 2014.

Additionally, her film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), which premiered at the 2006 Toronto Film Festival, was released by The Weinstein Co. in theaters in the fall of 2013.

Heard resides in Los Angeles, where she is actively involved with Amnesty International. In 2015, she married actor Johnny Depp, and the two divorced in 2017.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp sues ex-wife Amber Heard for $50M, claiming defamation, affair with Elon Musk
snippet.description:
Amber Heard, and Johnny Depp arrive at the 27th annual Palm Springs International Film Festival Awards Gala in Palm Springs, Calif., Jan. 2, 2016. (Associated Press) 
Actor Johnny Depp has filed a $50 million defamation lawsuit against his ex-wife, actress Amber Heard, accusing her of making allegations of domestic abuse in order to advance her career. 
In the lawsuit, which was filed in Virginia on Friday, Depp cites an article that Heard wrote for the Washington Post about domestic abuse. 
The lawsuit also contains Depp‚Äôs allegation that Heard began an affair with Tesla founder Elon Musk just one month after Depp and Heard got married in 2015. 
Heard‚Äôs attorney, Eric M. George, responded to the lawsuit in a statement to People magazine. 
JOHNNY DEPP AND AMBER HEARD AVOID AWKWARD ENCOUNTER DURING COMIC-CON 
‚ÄúThis frivolous action is just the latest of Johnny Depp‚Äôs repeated efforts to silence Amber Heard,‚Äù George said. ‚ÄúShe will not be silenced.‚Äù 
‚ÄúThis frivolous action is just the latest of Johnny Depp‚Äôs repeated efforts to silence Amber Heard. She will not be silenced.‚Äù 
‚Äî Eric M. George, attorney for Amber Heard 
Depp‚Äôs attorney, Adam Waldman, then responded to George‚Äôs statement. 
‚ÄúTelling media ‚Äòthey want to silence Amber Heard‚Äô doesn‚Äôt sound like a denial by Ms. Heard of Mr. Depp‚Äôs 40-page, evidence-packed complaint,‚Äù Waldman said in a statement to People. 
‚ÄúWe hardly intend to silence Ms. Heard,‚Äù Waldman continued. ‚ÄúTo the contrary, we intend to subpoena and compel evidence from her, her three hoax-assisting friends, and Elon Musk. We look forward to holding the overwhelming video, photographic and eyewitness evidence we finally possess up against Amber Heard‚Äôs (so far silent) attempts to explain the inexplicable.‚Äù 
"We hardly intend to silence Ms. Heard. To the contrary, we intend to subpoena and compel evidence from her, her three hoax-assisting friends, and Elon Musk." 
‚Äî Adam Waldman, attorney for Johnny Depp 
Depp‚Äôs complaint says that although Heard did not use Depp‚Äôs name in the Post article, it was clear she was referring to him. The lawsuit calls her ongoing allegations of domestic abuse "categorically and demonstrably false." 
"They were part of an elaborate hoax to generate positive publicity for Ms. Heard and advance her career," the lawsuit says, claiming that "she is the perpetrator." 
The suit said Depp, 55, has suffered financial losses because of the accusations, including being dropped from his role as Capt. Jack Sparrow in the "Pirates of the Caribbean" films. 
In her article, published in the Post in December, Heard, 32, also says she lost an acting role and contract with a major fashion brand because she went public with her claims of abuse. 
Video
"I spoke up against sexual violence ‚Äî and faced our culture's wrath," the 32-year-old actress wrote, adding that she felt as those she was "on trial in the court of public opinion." 
Video

snippet.title: Johnny Depp goes after Amber Heard with $50M defamation suit - Latest News
snippet.description: Johnny Depp goes after Amber Heard with $50M defamation suit - Latest News  ¬†Johnny Depp has had a lot of legal run-ins the past few years, but this time it is distinctly personal. ¬†Almost three years after news of the breakdown of ‚ÄúThe Pirates of the Caribbean‚Äù star‚Äôs marriage to Amber Heard hit the public record, Depp is now suing his ex-wife and ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù star for $50 million for defamation. ¬†‚ÄúMs. Heard is not a victim of domestic abuse, she is a perpetrator,‚Äù says the suit in reaction to an op-end the actress penned for The Washington Post in mid-December last year.‚Äú I had the rare vantage point of seeing, in real time, how institutions protect men accused of abuse,‚Äù Heard said. ‚ÄúI spoke up againstual violence ‚Äî and faced our culture‚Äôs wrath. That has to change‚Äù entitled Post piece, which never actually mentioned Depp by name but clearly didn‚Äôt have to ‚Äì at least not for this lawsuit. ¬†‚ÄúMr. Depp never abused Ms. Heard, the compensatory damages and punitive damages seeking complaint from the actor goes on to say. ‚ÄúHer allegations against him were false when they were made in 2016,‚Äù it adds in reference to the claims that Heard made in the couple‚Äôs short-lived union. ¬†A marriage that ended with a temporary restraining order against Depp and later a $7 million settlement, that Heard donated to charity. Having long since denied the abuse allegations, the Hollywood Vampires guitarist clearly now thinks there was more going on.‚Äú They were part of an elaborate hoax to generate positive publicity for Ms. Heard and advance her career,‚Äù Friday‚Äôs lawsuit postulates of the allegations of Depp‚Äôs violent misconduct. ¬†‚ÄúThis frivolous action is just the latest of Johnny Depp‚Äôs repeated efforts to silence Amber Heard,‚Äù the actress‚Äô attorney Eric M. George told Deadline. ‚ÄúShe will not be silenced.‚Äù ¬†‚ÄúMr. Depp‚Äôs actions prove he is unable to accept the truth of his ongoing abusive behavior, the Browne George Ross LLP partner added. ¬†‚ÄúBut while he appears hell-bent on achieving self destruction, we will prevail in defeating this groundless lawsuit and ending the continued vile harassment of my client by Mr. Depp and his legal team.‚ÄùRepresentatives for Depp did not respond to request for comment on the filing.However, if their past legal entanglements are any indication, expect the ambassador on women‚Äôs rights at the American Civil Liberties Union to not enter her own POV into the docket soon. ¬†This latest suit comes against the backdrop of Depp still battling it out on several other legal fronts. Despite a big win last summer, one of those battles include a $30 million malpractice action against the actor‚Äôs ex-attorneys at Bloom Hergott Diemer Rosenthal LaViolette Feldman Schenkman & Goodman LLP. snippet.title: Johnny Depp sues ex-wife for $50 million in defamation suit
snippet.description:
(12 Apr 2019) JOHNNY DEPP SUES EX-WIFE FOR $50 MILLION IN DEFAMATION SUIT
Actress Amber Heard is asking a judge to dismiss a $50 million defamation lawsuit her ex-husband Johnny Depp filed over a Washington Post op-ed she wrote about domestic violence.
¬†¬†
In the motion filed Thursday (11 APRIL 2019) in Fairfax, Virginia, Heard's lawyers reiterate allegations that Depp abused her and include exhibits such as photos of her with bruised face and scarred arms.
¬†¬†
Depp's lawsuit, filed last month, said the domestic-abuse allegations are "categorically and demonstrably false."
¬†¬†
Heard's Post piece said the culture punished her about being a victim of domestic violence, and she argued for changed attitudes.
¬†¬†
It didn't me mention Depp's name or describe any incidents, but Depp's lawsuit states it was clear Heard was talking about him and it hurt his career.
¬†¬†
Messages seeking comment from Depp's attorney were not immediately returned.

Johnny Depp talks backlash from Amber Heard abuse allegations
Johnny Depp is opening up about the tumultuous year he's had after his ex-wife, actress Amber Heard, accused him of physically abusing her. 
Johnny Depp‚Äôs bandmate Alice Cooper came to the actor‚Äôs defense and said the majority of the headlines concerning Depp‚Äôs physical appearance and health were ‚Äújust bull.‚Äù 
Cooper, who is in the rock group "Hollywood Vampires" with Depp, told Billboard that he‚Äôs never seen Depp ‚Äúhappier‚Äù amid the ongoing case involving ex-wife Amber Heard and reports of his health. 
‚ÄúAll the stuff you heard last year about Johnny, 99 percent was just bull,‚Äù Cooper said. ‚ÄúI've never seen him look better in my life. I've never seen him happier. I've never heard him play better, and the way the press would have it is 'he's a total destruction and ready to die.' Totally not true.‚Äù

Cooper said the band‚Äôs upcoming album will include songs by Depp about his frustrations over the abuse allegations against him. 
‚ÄúI'm spewing his venom on this album, which is kind of good,‚Äù Cooper said. 
Depp filed a $50 million defamation lawsuit against Heard earlier this month, claiming she accused him of domestic abuse to advance her career. The lawsuit cites an article by Heard published on the Washington Post in which she talks about her experience with domestic abuse. The ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù star also claimed Heard‚Äôs relationship with Tesla founder Elon Musk began a month after the former couple got married in 2015. 
The actor also sparked concerns last June when photos emerged of him looking frail and gaunt. Fans questioned whether Depp‚Äôs emaciated appearance was due to his public divorce with Heard, which a source previously told Fox News was ‚Äúmentally draining‚Äù and took a toll financially for the actor.

 The fact that Guyger, a white police officer, shot and killed Jean, an unarmed black man, and was initially only charged with manslaughter resulted in protests and accusations of racial bias

snippet.title: Building a Referral Network by Being Present with Amber Gough of Talent Fusion Point
snippet.description:
That's a really good question, typically through referral. I mean I get most of my business comes through referral-based in connecting with people they know, working well with my clients making a difference for them, and then they want to make a big impact for one of their friends who has a business or someone that they know in their network. So very much so through referral base. 

Reb Risty Great, great. Well, so the marketing question for you is in your business obviously its very relationship-based. How do you build your referral network? How are you going out in marketing yourself to grow your business? 

Amber Gough  I am a big believer in and connecting with people. And so when I am out networking whether it be through just socializing or in a formal networking setting I really strive to be very present. And so in the moment with the person - a matter of fact, my logo is a symbol for presence - and I believe so firmly I show up authentically and I, if I'm listening to someone, really hearing them, what's what their concerns are, what they're really - what their actual needs are, and connecting them with it as people. Then I'm able to serve them better, at whether that be through my business or referring to them to somebody else or what have you. So, I think that my ability to just show up and show someone that I care and that I'm really there with them in that moment, builds trust and people are more likely to refer people to me. 

Reb Risty: You know another good way to build trust is through webinars. So Amber was just sharing with me, that you've had some success with that. I'd love to hear about what you're doing, what your approach is with webinars. 

Amber Gough Absolutely. I was fortunate enough that through networking and connecting with someone. One of my friends, I built that trust, and she said you know, and she does a lot of webinars speaker, author, and she said you need to be teaching webinars. And she connected me with a few organizations that are H.R. (human resources base) which is very big in my industry and my primary contact, and connected me in. And fortunately, they set it up. It's very seamless and easy it only takes my time essentially in building out the PowerPoint presentation and the content in which I'm teaching, and then I'm able to present to as many as, my most recent webinar 800 people dialed in across the nation. 

Reb Risty  Wow

Amber Gough Yeah. Huge, huge footprint. And then others can actually access that as well through going to their website. I can present that content. It's fantastic. And through that typically at the end of the webinar throughout it you're offering some sort of freebie so it might be a survey or some way of analyzing purpose, you know alignment with a candidate in a company and then they reach out to you. It opens the door to a conversation and you're able to oftentimes convert that into clients. So, it's really powerful. Plus, it's fun. If you're talking about something, you're passionate about and enjoy it can be really, really fun as well. So, I love it.

Reb Risty [00:05:26] That's great, yeah. That's some great advice. I know obviously video as we're doing now podcasting, webinars are becoming more popular because people are just seeking information in a, I think in a different way, and they're trying to educate themselves, first, before they make decisions. So that's really, really neat. I love to hear that's working. 

Amber Gough [00:05:46] Absolutely and it's such a differentiator of being a subject matter expert too. Like this is what I know this is what I can do. I'm a subject matter expert so people are more likely to come to you, and it kind of builds that trust. 

Amber Gough It's really powerful. 

Reb Risty Right. Well, you heard it here. Content, subject matter expert, referral network, are all very important, especially in professional services. Amber if somebody wants to contact you learn more about what you're doing or how you're doing, how, what's the best way to reach you? 

Amber Gough Number one for recruiters: LinkedIn, always. Just look up "Amber Gough | G-O-U-G-H" or of course my website and my email which is talentfusionpoint.com and my email is amber@talentfusionpoint.com.

snippet.title: Amber Guyger Testifies And Is Cross Examined In Her Murder Trial Concerning Botham Jean
snippet.description:
Ex-Dallas police officer Amber Guyger cried two times while she was being questioned during her murder trial on Friday.

She had testified for less than an hour the first time she broke down in tears. Guyger, who had previously showed little emotion and talked in very subdued tones while on the witness stand, suddenly began to cry and weep loudly.

State District Judge Tammy Kemp sent the jury out of the courtroom to allow Guyger to take a 10-minute break.

About an hour later, Guyger began crying again and telling people that she was sorry and that she will have to live with her decision to shoot an innocent man for the rest of her life.

‚ÄúNo police officer would ever want to hurt an innocent person,‚Äù Guyger said.

Guyger, 31, is charged with murder in the Sept. 6, 2018, death of her neighbor Botham Shem Jean, 26. She has said that she mistook Jean‚Äôs apartment for her own and thought he was an intruder.

Guyger, who was in uniform but off duty at the time of the shooting, was fired from the Dallas police force.

Guyger approached the door with her key in hand and stopped, she said.

‚ÄúI saw it [the door] was cracked open,‚Äù Guyger testified. ‚ÄúI heard someone moving around in my apartment. There was a loud shuffling around. But me putting the key in the lock is pushing the door open.‚Äù

Guyger said she was scared to death and her heart rate sky-rocketed.

‚ÄúI compare it to being in a car wreck,‚Äù Guyger said. ‚ÄúRight before you are going to hit, everything freezes up inside your body. It‚Äôs just fear, fear, fear.‚Äù

Guyger said she saw a shadow of a figure in the back of the dark room and yelled at him.

‚ÄúLet me see your hands! Let me see your hands! And I drew my service revolver,‚Äù Guyger said. ‚ÄúThen I saw him coming toward me. I thought he was going to kill me. He was yelling, ‚ÄòHey, hey, hey!‚Äô in an aggressive voice.‚Äù

She said the figure was pacing back and forth near the back wall. Only a matter of seconds passed. Guyger fired two rounds.

Guyger said she shot because she believed the man was going to kill her. He was coming toward her at a ‚Äúfast-paced‚Äù walk, she said, and she couldn‚Äôt see his hands and didn‚Äôt know if he had a weapon. Police later found Jean was unarmed, and prosecutors say he was never a threat to Guyger.

After shooting Jean, Guyger testified, she then walked to the kitchen counter area and that‚Äôs when she started to realize that she was in the wrong apartment and she had shot someone innocent.

‚ÄúBefore that I was only focused on the threat,‚Äù Guyger said.

Guyger testified that as she walked toward Jean‚Äôs fallen body she realized that she had no idea who he was.

‚ÄúI was kneeling down next to him and I called 911,‚Äù Guyger said. ‚ÄúI knew I had shot him. I didn‚Äôt know where he was shot on his body.‚Äù

Guyger testified that she was calling 911 with one hand and doing chest compressions on Jean with her other hand. When questioned by a prosecutor, she said she stopped her attempts at first aid several times. Guyger told the jury that she walked outside so she could see where she was and give the location to the 911 dispatcher.

snippet.title: Amber Heard describes the moment she came out to her religious parents: 'It was just tears, tears'
snippet.description:
close
Video
Amber Heard talks superhero roles for women
Amber Heard stars as Mera in 'Aquaman' and sees the industry turning a corner when it comes to superhero roles for women. 
Amber Heard revealed she is bisexual in 2010, but she recently revealed at an SXSW panel that coming out to her religious parents was the hardest part of her coming out story. 
The ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù actress spoke at the ‚ÄúMaking Change on and Off the Screen‚Äù panel at SXSW Saturday, where she told the difficult story of getting her parents to understand her sexuality and think outside a ‚Äúbinary system.‚Äù 
AMBER HEARD DENIES REPORT THAT JOHNNY DEPP ACCUSED HER OF DEFECATING IN THEIR MARITAL BED 
‚ÄúI am from Austin, Texas. My dad is out of central casting Texan. Good Southern man, and I was raised in a religious home,‚Äù she told the crowd (via People). ‚ÄúAnd being an outspoken lesbian, atheist, vegetarian, I remember when I told them about my relationship, that I was in love with this woman, and at the beginning of that it was just tears, tears.‚Äù

snippet.description:
#AmberHeard #JohnnyDepp #AmberHeardJohnnyDepp #AmberHeardbisexual

Hidden Radar

Amber Heard said: 'Parents cry when they know I love homosexuals'

Actress 'Aquaman' remembers difficult days when she first revealed to her family a bisexual.

Talking at the South By Southwest art festival in Texas on March 9, Amber Heard revealed that the most awkward thing about "coming out" about your gender is the moment facing your loved one. "They don't know how to accept it because of them, it's beyond normal standards," Amber said.

"I am from Austin, Texas. My father is a native of this region, a standard Southern man and I was raised in a pious family. As a gay, atheist and vegetarian, I remember When I told my parents about a relationship with a girl, they cried non-stop. "

Amber Heard is openly bisexual (love both men and women) in 2010 at the GLAAD awards ceremony (the award honors individuals and collectives contributing to the LGBT community). At that time, she was in love with female photographer Tasya Van Ree.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's London Fields Scores Worst Box Office Opening In A Decade
snippet.description: With the worst box office opening in a decade, Amber Heards crime mystery  London Fields had audiences staying home. The film, based on a 1989 novel written by Martin Amis, premiered this past Friday after several delays due to a heated legal dispute within the production team. Production on  London Fields  began in London in 2013 after the project had been shuffled between several directors for a decade. With Billy Bob Thornton ( Fargo ), Amber Heard ( Justice League ), and Cara Delevingne ( Suicide Squad ) attached, the projectappeared to be finally taking shape. The story focuses on Heards character,a femme fatale named Nicola Six, who preconceives her own death - a murderat the hands ofone of her three lovers. Related: 15 Movies Coming Out This Year (And 15 Coming Out In 2019) Unfortunately,  London Fields  continued its downward trajectory at the box office. THR is reporting thatthecrime mystery had the second worst opening for a wide release since 1980, following closely behind the 2008 biographical drama,  Proud American . According to initial estimates, the film raked in a meager $160K from 613 theaters. Its weekend earnings wont be finalized until Monday; however, with its 0% rating on Rotten Tomatoes its unlikely London Fields will recover. This post-release disaster is not the first of the films setbacks, as botha legal battle and a restraining ordermarred London Fields  journey to the box office. Heard married  Johnny Depp -whos featured in a cameo in  London Fields  -atthestart of shooting, but eventually filed a temporary restraining order against him due to abusive behavior in May 2016. That previous September, London Fields was headed for the 2015  Toronto Film Festival  until director, Matthew Cullen, and a producer became embroiled in a legal dispute. This was followed by another legal battlewhena producer sued Heard andshe countersued on behalf of several issues including violations to her nudity agreement. Every film faces an often long and winding road to the box office; unfortunately, London Fields  has faced a few more challenges than the average release and has not escaped unscathed. Perhaps the writing of Martin Amis was notsuitedfor a film adaptation or perhaps those who adapted it failed to grasp themeaning behind the source materialsapparent convolution. Either way, this adaptation has made box office history, just not the kind of history one hopes to make.Suffice it to say, though, things shouldgo much,  much  better for Heards next film,  Aquaman . Source: THR Tags: london fields

snippet.description:
Here's my first ever original song! It's called Yellow and I would describe it as "not your typical love song" in the sorts that it's my own story to tell. Thank you to the organizers, competitors, judges, and many other supportive members of the Just Jakes team who helped to put this year's first ever Cowichan Songsmith together!.

Here's my first ever original song! It's called Yellow and I would describe it as "not your typical love song" in the sorts that it's my own story to tell. Thank you to the organizers, competitors, judges, and many other supportive members of the Just Jakes team who helped to put this year's first ever Cowichan Songsmith together!. 

July 13, 2019

Video credits to my mom :)

snippet.title: RAW VIDEO: Jury finds Amber Guyger guilty of murder in shooting death of Botham Jean
snippet.description:
The jury has found Amber Guyger guilty of murder in the shooting death of her neighbor Botham Jean on Sept. 6, 2018.

The jury reached the verdict late Tuesday morning, a day after closing arguments were delivered by both the state and defense. 

"Yes Lord! You never failed me yet! #JusticeforBotham," wrote Allison Jean, Botham's mother, on her Facebook page shortly after she heard that Guyger was found guilty.

snippet.title: 2019 Community Ownership Awardee |  Amber Sloan | Neighborhood Allies Healthy Neighborhood Awards
snippet.description: Amber goes above and beyond to serve the Homewood community. Her passion is helping people to create better lives and better communities, especially in the neighborhood she calls home, Homewood. She is authentic and genuine in her approach, meeting people where they are at and ensuring their voice is heard. On any given day, you will find Amber speaking to teens to equip them with knowledge, helping families get their basic needs met, or advocating for political change to improve the lives of the most vulnerable. Her deep roots in the neighborhood combined with her commitment to save lives inspires many people on a daily basis and truly creates a better community for us all.

snippet.title: Amber Guyger Judge Tammy Kemp Knew Joshua Brown Needed Protection | "I'm Surprised He Came"
snippet.description:
Joshua Brown expressed he was in fear for his life. He was forced into the Amber Guyger trial via subpoena. Lee Merritt spoke on Full Circle Anderson Coopers show on CNN. He stated it‚Äôs likely Joshua‚Äôs past caught up with him, but nobody should be ruled out including Dallas PD. The courts knew Joshua Brown was in fear for his life. During Joshua‚Äôs Testimony there was an intermission for a break. Audio unintentionally was heard of Judge Tammy Kemp ‚Äúof course he‚Äôs here‚Äù ‚ÄúI‚Äôm surprised he came‚Äù They failed to protect this witness, especially having everything broadcasted live via stream. I personally feel this maybe he past catching up with him but everything needs to be looked into. Joshua Brown would have also been a witness testimony for the civil case. 

New York Post:
Brown fled the state for California, where he remained as the trial got underway, according to Meritt.
But prosecutors ‚Äúhounded him‚Äù and threatened to issue a warrant for his arrest if he didn‚Äôt appear in court. ‚ÄúSo he got on a plane and came straight from the airport to the courthouse,‚Äù Merritt said.
Once he arrived, Brown met with the judge in her chambers about his concerns, but ultimately ended up taking the stand, Meritt said

snippet.title: Witness in Amber Guyger Case Shot Dead in Dallas - Prison Talk Live Stream E130
snippet.description:
A witness in the murder trial of a white Dallas police officer who fatally shot her black neighbor has been killed in a shooting, the Dallas Morning News reported, citing authorities.

The newspaper reported that authorities said Joshua Brown, who lived in the same apartment complex as Amber Guyger and Botham Jean, was shot and killed Friday in Dallas. Guyger was still in her police uniform after a long shift when, according to her trial testimony, she mistook Jean‚Äôs apartment for her own one floor below and shot him after pushing open his unlocked door and thinking he was a burglar.

Brown, 28, testified in Guyger‚Äôs trial about the September 2018 night that Jean was killed, saying he was in a hallway on the fourth floor, where he and Jean lived. He said he heard what sounded like ‚Äútwo people meeting by surprise‚Äù and then two gunshots.
.

snippet.title: Amber Heard, Julianne Moore, Elle Fanning add  star power to 'Les Miserables' red carpet premiere in
snippet.description:
(15 May 2019) AMBER HEARD, ELLE FANNING AMONG STARS ON RED CARPET FOR LADJ LY'S 'LES MISERABLES'¬†¬†
Amber Heard, Julianne Moore and Elle Fanning added some star power to the "Les Miserables" red carpet on Wednesday (15 MAY 2019) on the Croisette.
The French drama in competition at Cannes Film Festival is the feature debut of Ladj Ly, who was joined on the red carpet by most of his cast including Djibril Zonga, Alexis Manenti, Damien Bonnard and Steve Tientcheu. 
"Les Miserables" follows 48 hours in the life of a team of cops and the people in the neighborhood they police. 
It's among 21 films competing for the Palme D'Or which will be awarded on May 25.

American actress
Amber Laura Heard is an American actress and model. Born and raised in Texas, Heard made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

"Ich war wie gel√§hmt von dem Monster" 
04.01.2019

Wann immer er es nahm, machte ich mir Sorgen um uns beide. Er wurde eine v√∂llig andere Person, oft wahnhaft und gewaltt√§tig," wird aus Heards Anklage zitiert. 
Johnny Depp streitet Vorwurf der h√§uslichen Gewalt ab 
Amber Heards Vorw√ºrfe gegen ihren 55-j√§hrigen Ex-Mann wiegen schwer. Ob die erneut getroffenen Anschuldigungen der Schauspielerin gegen den Hollywood-Star der Wahrheit entsprechen, soll nun endg√ºltig vor Gericht gekl√§rt werden. snippet.title: Weam, a SAMS Thalassemia patient in Jordan
snippet.description: During our mission to Jordan with SAMS Goodwill Ambassador Amber Heard this April, we met 12-year-old Weam. Weam is a dialysis patient who suffers from a life-threatening condition called thalassemia. She and 12 other children living in Jordan‚Äôs al-Zaatari Refugee Camp have not received needed treatments due to high costs and budget cuts earlier this  year. We followed up with Weam in July to check on her progress and her hopes for the future.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Biography
snippet.description: Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress and model. Born and raised in Texas, Heard made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

snippet.title: Amber Heard Has Filed New Allegations That Johnny Depp Abused Her During Drug-Fueled Rages
snippet.description:
Amber Heard has filed new allegations against her ex-husband Johnny Depp, saying in court documents that he choked, hit, her during violent drug-fueled rages.The 32-year-old Aquaman actor said Depp abused alcohol and drugs ‚Äî both illegal and prescription ‚Äî during their relationship and became a "totally different person, often delusional and violent," including threatening to kill her, 
According to Amber Heard that she has written on her court documents has said After consuming eight MDMA tablets in Australia in 2015, johhny Depp choked amber Heard and then slammed her into a countertop,. Depp also accidentally cut off the tip of his fingertip on broken glass in the aftermath, and then wrote messages on a mirror in blood using his severed finger, the court documents state.
During their divorce proceedings in 2018, Heard accused Depp of hitting her in the face with a cellphone and pulling her hair.Also johnney Depp has said that she punched him on the face twice 
Heard also says that Depp got drunk on a private plane in May 2014 and started throwing things at her because he was angry about a romantic scene she filmed with actor James Franco for the 2015 film The Adderall Diaries.
 
"Instead of reacting to his behavior, I simply moved seats," "That didn‚Äôt stop him. He pushed a chair at me as I walked by, yelled at me, ‚Äô"At some point, I stood up, and Johnny kicked me in the back, causing me to fall over. Johnny threw his boot at me while I was on the ground."
Depp allegedly wrote an apology text message ‚Äî Depp appeared as "Steve" in her phone as a privacy measure ‚Äî after the plane incident, saying that his "illness somehow crept up and grabbed" him.
Heard admitted in the documents that shortly after their return to Los Angeles, she punched Depp when she feared he would hurt her sister.
During another fight in their Los Angeles apartment in December 2015, Heard says, "He slapped me hard, grabbed me by my hair, and dragged me from a stairwell to the office to the living room to the kitchen. In the process, he pulled large chunks of hair and scalp out of my head."

In the motion filed in the Circuit Court of Fairfax, Virginia, Heard goes into harrowing detail about more than a dozen alleged incidents before and during their rocky one-year marriage in which she claims the actor was high on drugs or alcohol, became ‚Äúthe Monster‚Äù and punched, slapped, kicked, spat on and choked her. There are also details about Depp allegedly head-butting Heard and pulling her hair so hard that chunks of her scalp came out. 
Depp has denied the abuse, and the allegations have appeared in the couple‚Äôs divorce and other court documents. HuffPost has reached out to Depp‚Äôs publicist for comment. 
John Shearer via Getty Images 
Johnny Depp and Amber Heard attend at the Grammy Awards in 2016. 
In the court papers obtained by the New York Post‚Äôs Page Six, Heard claims that Depp‚Äôs substance abuse issues would trigger a personality they both referred to as ‚Äúthe Monster,‚Äù like on a morning in May 2014 in which the couple, who were dating at the time, traveled from Boston to Los Angeles on a private jet: 
On the flight, Johnny ordered the flight attendants to give him an oxygen tank, and drank heavily. Johnny‚Äôs handlers told me that he was upset that I was filming a movie with a romantic scene with James Franco the day before. Soon, Johnny began to throw objects at me. Instead of reacting to his behavior, I simply moved seats. That didn‚Äôt stop him. He provocatively pushed a chair at me as I walked by, yelled at me, and taunted me by yelling out the name ‚ÄúJames Franco.‚Äù 
Heard states that at one point during the flight, she stood up and Depp kicked her in the back. She says she fell to the floor, Depp threw a boot at her and continued to insult her until he went to the bathroom and passed out inside. 
Heard also elaborated on an incident she said occurred a month after their February 2015 marriage, in which Depp, who was supposed to be clean, went on a sleepless, three-day ecstasy bender in Australia: 
Johnny told me that I had not explicitly forbidden him from taking ecstasy. The argument heated up, and Johnny pushed me, slapped me, and shoved me to the ground before I retreated to a locked bedroom. 
Heard then goes into explicit detail about the abuse she said she endured during those three days, alleging she was hit, shoved and choked numerous more times. During their fights, Heard said Depp ‚Äúshoved me into a ping pong table that collapsed underneath me,‚Äù threw bottles of alcohol at her and through the window, breaking panels, and at one point pulled off her nightgown. ‚ÄúI was naked and b

snippet.title: Love Island's Amber Gill, Anna Vakili and Yewande Biala are 'not sure' if they will watch new winter
snippet.description: They rose to fame on the summer series of Love Island.¬†But winner Amber Gill and her BFF's Anna Vakili and Yewande Biala admitted they're not sure if they will watch the brand new winter series of the hit ITV2 show.¬†It comes after Caroline Flack, 40, stepped down as host after being charged with assaulting her toyboy boyfriend Lewis Burton, 27, at her London home earlier this month.¬†¬†   When asked by Ben Shepherd: 'Will you watch winter series?', the host was met with deadly silence.¬† Amber was the first to answer: 'I will be, yeah, I am going to try,' while Anna, 29, rather unconvincingly said: 'I am going to try, see it from a different perspective. Now you‚Äôve been in it, it‚Äôs different, you see it all.'¬†During their appearance, the girls also spoke about the advice they would give to any islanders.¬†¬†  Amber said: 'What I would do differently if I could turn back time, don‚Äôt take everything to heart or too seriously.¬†'Take it more lighthearted and fun. I kept it real, I am not sure if that is a good or bad thing.'Yewande added: 'Just enjoy it, everyone said to me, enjoy it, I didn‚Äôt understand. When you come out, you realise I‚Äôve had the most amazing experience not everyone gets to have. Enjoy each day, be happy and just enjoy.'   Amber, who shortly split from Greg O'Shea after winning the show, concluded: 'Just keep it real, always be yourself. Stay true to yourself, don‚Äôt be hung up on winning, just stick to what feels right.'¬†The trio's appearance comes after Caroline pleaded not guilty to assaulting her boyfriend, 27, at Highbury Magistrates' Court on Monday.¬†Caroline and her partner were both allegedly covered in blood when police arrived at their flat in Islington, North London, on December 12 - with one officer describing the chaotic scene as 'like a horror movie'.   On Monday she pleaded not guilty to common assault and was released on bail until her trial in March but is not allowed to contact Lewis.¬†The presenter was accused of 'going mad' and smashing a glass after looking at texts which made her think Lewis was cheating - with him saying in a 999 call that she 'tried to kill me, mate', Highbury Corner Magistrates' Court heard.Lewis was said to have been 'almost begging the operator to send help' with his face 'covered in blood', while Caroline - who has now been replaced as Love Island host by Laura Whitmore - allegedly had two cuts to her wrist.¬†¬†After being taken into custody, ITV host Caroline - whom the court heard was 'manipulative' towards Lewis and accused him of ruining her life - allegedly flipped over a table and had to be restrained on the ground by police.¬†¬†In the wake of the drama, Caroline stepped down from her hosting duties and Laura Whitmore was announced as her replacement.

snippet.title: Latest Technology News - WSJ publisher agrees to supply headlines for Facebook news tab
snippet.description:
--- Amber criticises Instagram policy on female nipples with Momoa's edited pic --- 
  Actress Amber Heard on Sunday criticised Instagram's guidelines, that restrict showing female nipples, by posting an edited picture of actor Jason Momoa in which his chest was visible. "This picture meets Instagram's nudity guidelines & careful gender policies," she captioned Momoa's picture. Amber's post comes a month after Instagram censored the original picture in which her nipple was visible.
 --- WSJ publisher agrees to supply headlines for Facebook news tab --- 
  Facebook has reached a deal with News Corp to feature headlines from the Wall Street Journal, other Dow Jones media properties and the New York Post in its upcoming dedicated news tab. Other publications like Buzzfeed News and Washington Post have also reached similar deals, the WSJ reported. Under the agreement, the publications will reportedly be paid a licensing fee.
 --- Neat idea but won't happen: JPMorgan CEO on Facebook's Libra --- 
  Speaking about Facebook's proposed cryptocurrency 'Libra', Jamie Dimon, the CEO of American financial services firm JPMorgan Chase, said that it was "a neat idea that will never happen." Referring to his own firm's stablecoin JPM Coin, Dimon added Facebook wasn't "the first" in coming up with the idea. Recently, several companies including Visa and Mastercard dropped their backing for Libra.

snippet.description: Rita Ora, Amber Heard and Bella Hadid light up the red carpet at the Cannes Film Festival - Latest N STARS including Rita Ora, Bella Hadid and Amber Heard continued the parade of non-stop glamour at the Cannes Film Festival today. ¬†Even Liam Payne dropped by, with the singer tonight attending a luxurious dinner alongside close pal Rita, Nick Jonas and Priyanka Chopra. Rex Features8 Bella Hadid came in the same shade as the carpet The Mega Agency8 She was loving her scarlet gown at today's premiere ¬†Model Bella, 22, was among the first to arrive at today's premiere for Penelope Cruz movie Pain and Glory in a scarlet Grecian gown. ¬†Amber, 33, was close behind in an ruffled silk gown with leather thigh-high boots, waving to the crowds who were craning their necks for a glimpse of red-carpet glamour. ¬†Meanwhile the film's star Penelope, 45, wore a large blue and white lace gown, laughing with her co-star Antonio Banderas as they strolled in. ¬†The Mask of Zorro actor, 58, held hands with his banker girlfriend Nicole Kimpel, 38, as the pair made their way in to watch the movie. snippet.title: Project EGG Show #232 - Amber Vilhauer
snippet.description:
Amber Vilhauer‚Äôs life's purpose is helping others feel seen, heard, loved and valued. Her career‚Äôs purpose is to help impact-driven business owners get their message out to the world in the most efficient and powerful way through digital marketing opportunities.

Before founding NGNG Enterprises with Amber Vilhauer (standing for NoGutsNoGlory) in 2007, Amber was an integral part of a multi-million dollar marketing company named Vector Marketing, while also attending the University of Arizona for Marketing and Graphic Design. As a young 20 year old, not only did Amber achieve the highest sales level in the company of Senior Field Sales Manager, she also moved through the management levels very quickly.

From her promotion of Assistant Manager after 3 short months, Amber went on to become a lead Sales Manager for her local district office. She was pursued to move to Denver for the position of Pilot Sales Manager, helping to run a division of 13 offices in 4 states. Amber trained new managers to open their own district office, was responsible for training and managing more than 30 receptionists in the division, all while continuing to recruit and train thousands of sales reps for the Denver district. Amber assisted in coordinating division-wide conferences throughout the year, regularly speaking in small workshop and 300-person conference settings.

At 25 years old, Amber was ready for her next challenge. She pivoted and organized the production of two powerful conferences designed to teach budding entrepreneurs how to grow their business online. As Amber connected with the speakers, some of the top online marketing experts of all time, her passion to test and refine their strategies was born.

Working one-on-one with her author, speaker and coach clients, Amber and her team have created more than 500 WordPress websites. Amber knows how a website needs to function in order to generate sales, build a fan base and attract long-term clientele. She works with clients to build a strong, branded social media presence, coaches each client on which manageable actions will help them achieve their online goals and then walks them through exactly how to do it.

Watch the full episode here: https://projectegg.co/amber-vilhauer

About The Project EGG Show:
The Project EGG Show is a video talk show that introduces you to entrepreneurs from around the world. It is broadcast from studios in Metairie, Louisiana to online platforms including YouTube, iTunes, Google Play, Spotify and Stitcher, and hosted by Ben Gothard.

Our goal is to give you a fresh, unscripted and unedited look into the lives of real entrepreneurs from around the globe. From billionaires to New York Times best selling authors to Emmy Award winners to Forbes 30 Under 30 recipients to TEDx speakers ‚Äì we present their real stories ‚Äì uncensored and uncut.

snippet.title: Aquaman Magazine Cover Reveals New Look at Arthur Curry & Mera
snippet.description: A new magazine cover for  Aquaman  shows another look atArthur Curry (Jason Momoa) and Mera (Amber Heard). Momoa made his DC debut in a limited capacity in Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice , but it was last years Justice League  that gave audiences a true introduction to his version of Aquaman. Most found his energetic portrayal to be a highlight of the film and only increased interest in his solo movie coming out this December. After just briefly seeing his home Atlantis, Aquaman  will completely dive into the vast mythology and various characters that inhabit it. While Aquaman  willhave plenty of scenes in the underwater kingdom, the main story will focus on Aquaman and Mera on an adventure. Theyre  searching for King Atlans trident  in the movie and will grow closer as the story progresses. There may not have been much of a relationship between them in Justice League , but theyre standing side by side in a new magazine cover. Related:  Aquamans Underwater Scenes Are Nothing Like Justice League Aquaman  director James Wan revealed on  Twitter  the official cover for the November issue of Total Film , which puts Momoa and Heard front and center. With water falling behind them, the two Atlanteans stand tall next to each other. Aquaman is still in his rocker, leather heavy look, while Mera is seen in her traditional green suit. This may not be the flashiest magazine cover thats ever been made, but its a solid one at least that focuses on the two main characters of Aquaman . The recently released  official  Aquaman  poster has a much better design to it for instance. Unlike that poster or the  extended  Aquaman  trailer  that was released, Momoa is not shown here in the classic orange and green suit we know hell wear. That costume may have made this cover pop a bit more, and also provide an up close look at the details. Well likely get plenty of other opportunities to see new looks of Aquaman  in the coming months as WB and DC kick the marketing campaign into full gear. DC could still release a proper second trailer in the coming weeks before the movie launches, but it will be multiple TV spots that, as usual, should provide the most new footage. At this point, many have already made up their minds about whether Aquaman  is a movie theyre interested in seeing or not, so it may take a surprise reveal to really change the interest level at this point. But, there have been no signs that the movie had any major problems or studio interference, so hopefully Aquaman  is going to end 2018 on a high note. Source:  James Wan Tags: aquaman

snippet.title: Key Witness in Amber Guyger Trial Murdered - LIVE COVERAGE
snippet.description:
Botham Jean's neighbor Joshua Brown, a key witness in the murder trial of Dallas police officer Amber Guyger, was shot and killed last night. Get the latest details in our LIVE COVERAGE.

There are no suspects yet and no known motive in Joshua Brown's murder. The shooting may have been a drive-by shooting -- a car was seen speeding away from where Brown was shot. Brown lived in the same apartment complex as Botham Jean and Amber Guyger, and was in the hallway and heard the gunshots last September when Amber Guyger shot and killed her neighbor Botham Jean. Guyger testified that she accidentally entered the wrong apartment and thought Jean was an intruder. A Dallas County jury convicted Guyger of murder this week, and Joshua Brown's testimony is seen as playing a key role in the trial. In this revealing conversation Amber Scorah opens the box into the psychology of religious belief to show how, exactly, religions and cults convince members that theirs is the one true religion, to the point, she admits, that she would have gladly died for her faith. As a third-generation Jehovah‚Äôs Witness, Amber Scorah had devoted her life to sounding God‚Äôs warning of impending Armageddon. She volunteered to take the message to China, where the preaching she did was illegal and could result in her expulsion or worse. Here, she had some distance from her community for the first time. Immersion in a foreign language and culture ‚Äî and a whole new way of thinking ‚Äî turned her world upside down, and eventually led her to lose all that she had been sure was true. As a proselytizer in Shanghai, using fake names and secret codes to evade the authorities‚Äô notice, Scorah discreetly looked for targets in public parks and stores. To support herself, she found work at a Chinese language learning podcast, hiding her real purpose from her coworkers. Now with a creative outlet, getting to know worldly people for the first time, she began to understand that there were other ways of seeing the world and living a fulfilling life. When one of these relationships became an ‚Äúescape hatch,‚Äù Scorah‚Äôs loss of faith culminated in her own personal apocalypse, the only kind of ending possible for a Jehovah‚Äôs Witness. Shunned by family and friends as an apostate, Scorah was alone in Shanghai and thrown into a world she had only known from the periphery ‚Äî with no education or support system. A coming of age story of a woman already in her thirties, this unforgettable memoir examines what it‚Äôs like to start one‚Äôs life over again with an entirely new identity. Scorah and Shermer also discuss:

‚Ä¢ the legals and logistics of writing a memoir
‚Ä¢ the rise of the nones and disbelief and why stories like hers provide social proof for living without religion
‚Ä¢ what Jehovah‚Äôs Witnesses believe and why they believe it
‚Ä¢ what it‚Äôs like to go door-to-door witnessing for a religion
‚Ä¢ Armageddon and what doomsayers do when the world doesn‚Äôt end
‚Ä¢ the mindset of the fundamentalist
‚Ä¢ why religions are obsessed with female sexuality
‚Ä¢ why religions forbid homosexuality
‚Ä¢ the psychology of deconversion
‚Ä¢ the problem of evil, or why bad things happen to good people
‚Ä¢ how she would try to talk someone out of joining ISIS
‚Ä¢ what it‚Äôs like to be expelled from a religion and be an apostate, and
‚Ä¢ how to start your life over when you‚Äôve lost everything.

Amber Scorah is a writer living in Brooklyn, NY. Her articles have been published in The New York Times, The Believer, and USA Today. Prior to coming to New York, Scorah lived in Shanghai, where she was creator and host of the podcast Dear Amber: An Insider‚Äôs Guide to Everything China. Leaving the Witness is her first book.

snippet.title: Botham Jean Neighbor, Key Witness in Amber Guyger Trial | Coincidence?
snippet.description:
A key witness in Amber Guyger's murder trial was shot and killed Friday evening at an apartment complex near Dallas' Medical District, authorities said.
Joshua Brown, a neighbor of Botham Jean's and Guyger at the South Side Flats apartments, was slain about 10:30 p.m. in the 4600 block of Cedar Springs Road. (Dallas News)

Joshua testified about what he saw and heard that night, saying he never heard Amber shout any commands that a police officer would normally shout at a suspect.

snippet.title: Amber Heard displays her punky new look as she flashes her toned abs at Puma x Balmain launch
snippet.description:
Take surveys. Get PAID: http://bit.ly/2XivKE0.  Amber Heard displays her punky new look as she flashes her toned abs at Puma x Balmain launch. She knows how to bring the glamour at stylish A-List events.

And Amber Heard showed off her punky new look at the Puma x Balmain launch event in Los Angeles on Thursday.

The Aquaman actress, 33, flashed her toned abs in a black and gold sports bra which featured the brand's name in shimmering gold lettering.¬†

The tiny garment drew the eye to her slender waist and teamed a glimpse of her decolletage, which was adorned with shimmering gold chains.

Amber paired her bra with floaty high-waisted red sequined trousers which had a strip of black and silver down the sides.

The star also donned a military style navy blue velvet jacket with statement shoulder pads and a gold trim around the sleeves.

She completed her look with accessories including a¬†black leather belt with a gold buckle and added¬†layers of gold chain necklaces.¬†

Amber wore her long blonde locks down for the star-studded event and let her curls cascade over her shoulders.¬†

She also added a bold red lipstick to accentuate her pretty features and complement her matching showstopping trousers.¬†¬†¬†

Joining Amber at the launch of Cara Delevingne's collaboration with Balmain, which was¬†inspired by the boxing ring, was¬†Eva Longoria, 44.

Eva¬†also sported the black and gold sports bra, paired with a black double-breasted tuxedo jacket, featuring gold buttons.

She completed the look with the black joggers, black stiletto booties and gold hoop earrings, matching her necklace, bracelet and watch.

Cara, 27, was also at the launch and looked fantastic in the same black sports bra as Amber and Eva and slim black joggers, featuring gold zippers on the sides.

Underneath the Hammersmith born British catwalk queen wore a pair of black fishnet stockings, pulled up over her tight tummy.¬†¬†

Amber's appearance comes after she celebrated

snippet.title: Aquaman 2019   Half Breed Bastard Abomination ‚Ä¶ and King
snippet.description:
#Aquaman
#mera
#atlantean
#king
#justiceleague
#jla
#jasonmomoa
#amberheard
#nicolekidman

Aquaman 2019 - Half Breed Bastard Abomination ‚Ä¶ and King

Today I will be talking about the movie Aquaman (2019)and give you my impressions about it. How  Arthur Curry (Aquaman) goes on a mission to find the Trident from the first Atlantean King, Atlan; how he falls in love with Mera (Amber Heard); how he faces both Black Manta and his half-brother, Orm Marius, the Ocean Master.

Before watching it, I didn't have a good impression about the movie judging by the Justice Leagues' movie that I didn't like and also because they've chosen Jason Momoa to be Aquaman. I was like ‚ÄúDrogo will be Aquaman? That will never work!‚Äù. Every time an actor is cast to interpret a character that he doesn't resemble, I get bad vibes. At least in my mind, he wasn't a good choice. The movie proved me wrong. 

I still can't get over the fact that they chose to change Aquaman's personality dramatically. I think I have to grow used to it. Aquaman in the comic books is a very formal, serious, knowledgeable character and that's the exact opposite of how the character is portrayed in the movie. In the big screen, the character is immature, dumb, show-off.

The characters felt like real people with real motivations. I didn't feel forced to swallow anything in it regarding they being who they were. Both heroes and villains were really well put together. The two main antagonists have in common the hate they feel towards Arthur. Orm Marius, the Ocean Master, Aquaman's brother who sees him as an inferior bastard half breed and David Kane (later Black Manta) who blames Arthur for his father's death.

The female heroine in this film, Mera, has all the features female characters nowadays showcase in movies. They know everything, they are extremely strong and super powerful, they have an answer for every situation. We don't get to see flashbacks of her training or anything about her growing up. This narrative, dumb, impulsive male character plus know-it-all female character is getting really old. It's the biggest clich√© in the 21st century.

The last scene will leave you without breath. The action sequence is just too eye candy and hypnotizing. The movie was a whole lot of fun and beautiful experience. The ticket to watch it was a good investment. I believe the movie is a complete package with all the elements you might like in a movie such as romance that seems real, the characters really look like they love one another, both couples Mera and Aquaman and Arthur's parents. The fight scenes were flawless, visual effects are amazing, everything looks so exotic and attractive. The villains were also great. The whole plot regarding Aquaman's and Ocean Master's mother, Atlanna (Nicole Kidman), was really moving.

I would like also to point out the relationship between Vulko (Willem Dafoe) and Arthur. He taught young Aquaman martial arts (including how to handle the Trident he was supposed to go after to claim his throne one day) and all the history of the Atlantean people.

Hopefully, we can see Aquaman in a new Justice League movie, this time with a better script and I also have my fingers crossed so they cast somebody to be the Green Lantern so we finally have a real Justice League movie, because in my humble opinion, without Green Lantern the League is not the League. It feels more like 6 characters joined together but not the real JLA.

The movie does a fantastic job both giving new life to the character's legacy and being respectful to the original source material. Do not miss the chance and go watch it if you haven't yet. I didn't feel the time passing when I was watching it.

snippet.title: Why Whale Poop Is So Expensive | So Expensive
snippet.description:
A small percentage of sperm whales produce ambergris, a clump of squid beaks and fatty secretions that scientists believe exits through the whales‚Äô bowels Ambergris is coveted by the fragrance industry for a chemical it contains called ambrien, which suspends smells in the air, and for its own unique scent Quality pieces of ambergris, which ambergris hunters snatch up as they wash ashore, can garner more than $7,000 a pound.

Following is a transcript of the video:

This is ambergris. It might look like a rock, but it‚Äôs actually a rare kind of whale poop. And it‚Äôs not cheap. Per gram, ambergris can cost more than silver‚Äî30 times more. If you‚Äôve ever worn perfume, well, I‚Äôve got some unsettling news. You may have misted yourself with animal waste. You see, for centuries, perfumers have been using ambergris to enhance their fragrances. Ambergris is essentially a clump of squid beaks bound by a fatty secretion. Over time, it balls up in the intestine of some sperm whales. And eventually ‚Ä¶. Out it goes. Now, in the strictest sense it‚Äôs not poop, but scientists think it likely exits the same way.

Christopher Kemp: ‚ÄúOne way or another, a big boulder of ambergris is released into the ocean and then floats for decades, or who knows how long.‚Äù 

In that time, the mass transforms from a sticky, dung-like substance into a hard, gray chunk. And this is what perfumers covet. For one, it contains a unique chemical called ambrein. It‚Äôs a fixative, which means it makes other smells in perfume last longer. But ambergris is also valued for something ‚Ä¶ more surprising: it‚Äôs smell. 

Christopher Kemp: ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs a bouquet of 20-30 chemical compounds that each have their own odor profile. One will smell sort of like mushrooms, one will smell a little bit like tobacco, one smells sort of like poop, one smells sort of like grass and hay.‚Äù

Sounds enticing, right? Apparently. Perfume designers use strong scents like these for the base note in their fragrances. And Base notes form the foundation of any perfume. They‚Äôre typically heavier, muskier smells, like what you get from a beaver‚Äôs castor sacs¬†or ‚Äî you guessed it ‚Äî ambergris. Roja Parfums, for example, has several expensive perfumes with base notes of ambergris like those in the Profumi D‚ÄôAmore collection. They sell for around $500 a bottle and are described as a ‚Äúpassionate love letter in fragrant form.‚Äù And while ambergris has all the makings for a great perfume, what really drives up the price tag is how rare it is. Scientists don‚Äôt know exactly why, but only about one percent of sperm whales produce the substance. In fact, researchers like Shane Gero who spend years studying sperm whales never see it.

Dr. Shane Gero: ‚ÄúI‚Äôve been collecting sperm whale poop for 15 to 16 years, but I haven‚Äôt collected anything that looks like ambergris.‚Äù

In some cases, lucky beachgoers will stumble upon it. In 2006, for example, a couple picked up a 32-pound piece on a beach in Australia. Media outlets later reported it could be worth nearly $300,000. But more often, ambergris hunters will get to it first. They track weather patterns and ocean currents to predict where it might end up. And once they find it, they sell it to brokers or perfumers for up to $7,200 a pound. 

Christopher Kemp: ‚ÄúThis is like gold to them. This is a real commodity. So they take it very seriously. They can be a bit aggressive, muscular and they really guard their secrets.‚Äù

But the commodity‚Äôs high price isn‚Äôt the only reason they do it. In some countries like the U.S., buying, selling, or even collecting ambergris is illegal. That‚Äôs because sperm whales are an internationally threatened species. 

Dr. Shane Gero: ‚ÄúBefore whaling started there were over a million sperm whales, and now we're down closer to a fifth of that.‚Äù

And while no whales are harmed in the collection of ambergris, Gero says it‚Äôs never a good idea to buy or sell products from an endangered species. But until we can replicate something that smells as good as whale poop, we probably will.

------------------------------------------------------

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Small Birth Family
snippet.description:
Amber Heard is a young Hollywood actress and a stunning model  whose professional career gains momentum due to extraordinary roles in movies and not only. She dreamt of becoming a famous film performer and in order to make this dream come true, she worked hard to pay for portfolio as well as filming in the studio. At 16, Amber moved to New York to start modeling career. Her bright beauty and beautiful body let her reach success without putting much effort. With the time, modeling sphere began weighing down and Heard moved to LA to ‚Äúconquer‚Äù the Hollywood. She started from playing bit roles in various projects such as The O.C. and Jack and Bobby. However, even these minor roles, helped her to get certain success and she was noticed by many film directors. In such a way, she can be seen in Friday Night Lights, North Country, Never Back Down, Pineapple Express, Magic Mike XXL and so many other works.

Amber‚Äôs father David is an actor in his own right. Knowing how hard an actor‚Äôs life is, he never wanted a daughter to be involved in the filmmaking industry. Nonetheless, it was Amber‚Äôs dream and she followed it. Later, David admitted that she made the right decision and is very proud of her. Both father and daughter can be seen at different events and on a red carpet together.

Meanwhile, a mother Paige is an IT person, who creates websites. In accordance with the actress, her mother is the best parent she could have ever had. Paige has always been supporting the daughter as well as taught her many things in life. 

The stunning movie star has a younger sister named Whitney, who is also an actress. Both sisters are extremely close and are often seen together at different parties and events. Nothing much is known about Whitney‚Äôs personal life, but there is a rumor that she is dating an actor Ryan Adams. 

That is all.
Don‚Äôt forget to subscribe to our channel.

Picture a hot night in the club, the party machinery is running at full speed and with every progressing hour, people are letting their hair down a little more. Let‚Äôs briefly sum up tonight‚Äôs impressions so far, shall we: ‚ÄúAss, titties, shots, ass, titties, drink‚Äù. And now this: a monster drop, hitting you right in the face and obliterating the dancefloor for a brief moment of eternity. 

Welcome to ‚ÄúMamma Mia‚Äù, the new single by HUGEL. Said lyrics can actually be heard in the song, delivered by Amber Van Day, who already featured in his last smasher ‚ÄúWTF‚Äù. Once again, her sexy, self-assured doesn‚Äôt fail to impress. Which is also owed to the song‚Äôs explicit lyrics, of course. In ‚ÄúMamma Mia‚Äù, HUGEL takes a dig at the shallow consumer- and party culture he witnesses every day playing the world‚Äôs top clubs. The world, he seems to tell us, is material and shallow. So let‚Äôs at least have a good party!

An outrageously good funk sample by James Brown, Prince-esque guitar licks and a wind section make for the foundation of this song, soon culminating in a foghorn drop you won‚Äôt get out of your head. Just like that Gucci bag you saw in that boutique earlier. Or was it Balenciaga? Doesn‚Äôt matter: ‚ÄúGucci Gang (Na na na) / Diamonds on me (Na na na) / More champagne papi‚Äù, Amber Van Day reminds us that our glass is empty yet again. Refill and proceed!
